entries.meaning: A form of motorsport that tests the skill and speed of a driver over a course marked out with traffic cones

verbs.description: autocross (third-person singular simple present autocrosses, present participle autocrossing, simple past and past participle autocrossed)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To take part in this sport.
examples: It may be helpful to join a car club that autocrosses because the club will have organized, periodic events that someone else has already set-up [sic] and coordinated.
